  "prompt": "Can a Singaporean stay in Malaysia indefinitely without a visa?",
  "response": "No, Singaporeans cannot stay in Malaysia indefinitely without a visa. While Singaporeans enjoy relatively easy travel between the two countries, there are still entry and stay restrictions:\n\n1. Short visits: Singaporeans can enter Malaysia visa-free for tourism or business purposes for up to 90 days.\n\n2. Longer stays: For stays beyond 90 days, Singaporeans need to apply for the appropriate visa or permit, such as:\n- Student Pass\n- Work Permit\n- Long-Term Social Visit Pass\n- Permanent Resident status\n\n3. Employment: To work in Malaysia, Singaporeans must obtain a valid work permit from the Malaysian immigration authorities.\n\n4. Permanent residency: To stay permanently, one must go through a specific application process and meet certain criteria.\n\nSo while Singaporeans have more convenient travel arrangements compared to many other nationalities, they cannot simply stay in Malaysia indefinitely without proper documentation or permissions.",
